co.cask.cdap.template.etl.api.batch

Class BatchSource<KEY_IN,VAL_IN,OUT>

  • java.lang.Object
    • co.cask.cdap.template.etl.api.batch.BatchConfigurable<BatchSourceContext>
      • co.cask.cdap.template.etl.api.batch.BatchSource<KEY_IN,VAL_IN,OUT>
  • Type Parameters:
    KEY_IN - the type of input key from the Batch run
    VAL_IN - the type of input value from the Batch run
    OUT - the type of output for the source
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Destroyable, PipelineConfigurable, StageLifecycle<BatchSourceContext>, Transformation<KeyValue<KEY_IN,VAL_IN>,OUT>

    @Beta
public abstract class BatchSource<KEY_IN,VAL_IN,OUT>
extends BatchConfigurable<BatchSourceContext>
implements Transformation<KeyValue<KEY_IN,VAL_IN>,OUT>, StageLifecycle<BatchSourceContext>
    Batch Source forms the first stage of a Batch ETL Pipeline. In addition to configuring the Batch run, it also transforms the key value pairs provided by the Batch run into a single output type to be consumed by subsequent transforms. By default, the value of the key value pair will be emitted. initialize(co.cask.cdap.template.etl.api.batch.BatchSourceContext), transform(co.cask.cdap.api.dataset.lib.KeyValue<KEY_IN, VAL_IN>, co.cask.cdap.template.etl.api.Emitter<OUT>) and destroy() methods are called inside the Batch Run while BatchConfigurable.prepareRun(T) and BatchConfigurable.onRunFinish(boolean, T) methods are called on the client side, which launches the Batch run, before the Batch run starts and after it finishes respectively.
